rComments: He would cancel class without warning, once using the excuse that he was volunteering. He seemed to treat being a prof as a hobby instead of as a job that affected the future of the students. I got an A in the class simply because I was a 4th year student and knew all the material already; the 2nd year students stood no chance at doing well.

Although he uses microphone, I still can't hear his low voice in class. He is very, very bad at explaining things and doesn't want to boom up grades. Although I got 90% on midterm, I still got an F at the end of the semester. Get ready to study on your own and learn the materials yourself.

He kept saying that it's his first time lecturing at university. The truth is: he just can't teach at all.  Can't explain concepts, can't solve a problem with clear steps, can't stick to the course schedule( canceled  classes 4 times), can't make exams.  AVOID HIM

2 expensive texts. Contents overlaps. No efforts for making course pack.
